timing_extrac...alidation_mode(25.10)    timing_extrac...alidation_mode(25.10)

Name
       timing_extract_model_exhaustive_validation_mode

Syntax
       timing_extract_model_exhaustive_validation_mode

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Enables extracted timing model (ETM) validation at the minimum and max-
       imum indices of the slew load indices.

       When  set  to  false,  the  ETM  validation  is done only for the input
       slews/output-loads that have been asserted on the design during  timing
       model extraction.

       When set to true, the software uses the "Extremity-Validation" (EV-ETM)
       methodology  that allows ETM to model the timing arcs in the design for
       a range of discrete input slews/output-loads,  thus  providing  a  more
       comprehensive validation.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

